Package jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.independent

Defines a Java object model for the OVAL Independent components.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EntityItemEngineType
    The EntityItemEngineType defines a string entity value that is restricted to an enumeration.
    EntityItemFamilyType
    The EntityItemFamily defines a string entity value that is restricted to a set of enumerations.
    EntityItemHashTypeType
    The EntityItemHashTypeType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that specify the different hash algorithms that are supported.

    The EntityItemLdaptypeType restricts a string value to a specific set of values that specify the different types of information that an ldap attribute can represent.

    EntityItemWindowsViewType

    EnvironmentVariable58Item
    This item stores information about an environment variable, the process ID of the process from which it was retrieved, and its corresponding value.
    EnvironmentVariable58Object
    The environmentvariable58 object is used by an environmentvariable test to define the specific environment variable(s) and process IDs to be evaluated.
    EnvironmentVariable58State
    The environmentvariable state contains three entities that are used to check the name of the specified environment variable, the process ID of the process from which the environment variable was retrieved, and the value associated with the environment variable.
    EnvironmentVariable58Test
    The environmentvariable test element is used to check an environment variable for the specified process, which is identified by its process ID, on the system.
    EnvironmentVariableItem Deprecated
    Deprecated as of version 5.8: Replaced by the environmentvariable58 item and will be removed in a future version of the language.

    EnvironmentVariableTest Deprecated

    FamilyItem
    This element stores high level system OS type, otherwise known as the family.
    FamilyObject
    The family object is used by a family test to define those objects to evaluate based on a specified state.
    FamilyState
    The family state contains a single entity that is used to check the family associated with the system.
    FamilyTest
    The family test is used to check the family a certain system belongs to.
    FileBehaviors
    The FileBehaviors type defines a number of behaviors that allow a more detailed definition of a set of files or file related items to collect.
    FileHash58Item
    The filehash58 item stores a hash value associated with a specific file.
    FileHash58Object
    The filehash58 object is used by a file hash test to define the specific file(s) to be evaluated.
    FileHash58State
    The filehash58 state contains entities that are used to check the file path, name, hash_type, and hash associated with a specific file.
    FileHash58Test
    The file hash test is used to check a specific hash type associated with a specified file.

    Ldap57Item

    LdapState
    The ldap state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified entries in an LDAP directory.
    LdapTest
    The LDAP test is used to check information about specific entries in an LDAP directory.
    Sql57Item

    Sql57Object

    TextfileContent
    Experimental: Is there any smart way to manage entities of OVAL Objects and States?
    TextfileContent54Behaviors
    The TextFileContent54Behaviors defines a number of behaviors that allow a more detailed definition of the textfilecontent54 object being specified.
    TextfileContent54Object
    The textfilecontent54 object is used by a textfilecontent test to define the specific block(s) of text of a file(s) to be evaluated.
    TextfileContent54State
    The textfilecontent54 state contains entities that are used to check the file path and name, as well as the text block in question and the value of the subexpressions.
    TextfileContent54Test
    The textfilecontent54 test is used to check the contents of a text file (aka a configuration file) by looking at individual blocks of text.
    TextfileContentItem
    The textfilecontent item looks at the contents of a text file (aka a configuration file) by looking at individual lines.
    TextfileContentObject Deprecated

    UnknownTest

    VariableItem
    This item stores information about OVAL Variables and their values.
    VariableObject  
    VariableState
    The variable state contains two entities that are used to check the var_ref of the specified varible and the value associated with it.
    VariableTest
    The variable test allows the value of a variable to be compared to a defined value.
    XmlfileContentItem
    This item stores results from checking the contents of an XML file.
    XmlfileContentObject
    The xmlfilecontent object is used by an XML file content test to define the specific piece of an xml file(s) to be evaluated.
    XmlfileContentState
    The xmlfilecontent state contains entities that are used to check the file path and name, as well as the xpath used and the value of the this xpath.
    XmlfileContentTest
    The xmlfilecontent test is used to explore the contents of an xml file.
